Function Reference/url to postid « WordPress Codex
-----------

Retrieve id of page/post given its url, or zero on failure. Can be
thought of as the opposite function of get\_permalink.

Note that this function does not return the post id for custom post
types (see Trac ticket
[\#19744](http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/19744 "http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/19744")).

When using this function to retrive the ID of an attachment, it is
required that the url provided be in the format of
example.com/?attachment\_id=N and will not work with the full URL. To
get the id from the full URL [see
this](http://pippinsplugins.com/retrieve-attachment-id-from-image-url/ "http://pippinsplugins.com/retrieve-attachment-id-from-image-url/")
for a work around.

Usage
-----

`  <?php $postid = url_to_postid( $url ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$url` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) The permalink to check.
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

 `(int)` 
:   ID of the post or page that resides at the given URL, or 0 on
    failure.

Change Log
----------

Since: 1.0.0

Source File
-----------

`url_to_postid()` is located in `wp-includes/rewrite.php`.

